<subSubSection id="C7FD8D9BA2D7251C9E744B744D4E2112" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="419F6EB134176575154DDAF56A8EECB8" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4EC7F363024FA399C529D05D5D0C6817" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Based on examined material, this species inhabits low to middle elevations (0-2000 m) in south China and north Vietnam. Recent Chinese specimens were collected in daylight in a mountainous area with evergreen forest and subtropical climate. Known from the Oriental Region only.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
